#ELLEFashion: “Even the smallest bindi had to feel like a statement.” With The Bindi Project, designer Meghna Khanna isn’t just reviving a cultural icon — she’s reshaping it. Handcrafted using upcycled leather and textile scraps, each piece blurs the line between jewellery and tradition, turning the humble bindi into a bold, expressive accessory. Rooted in sustainability and made with intention, these designs are named after goddesses and created to be kept, not discarded. “Don’t think of them as bindis,” Meghna says. “Think of them as jewellery.” Head to the 🔗 in bio to read more
.

latestPosts.caption:
❣️Just midweek hello  there! 🙋🏾‍♀️
Hope you’re getting thru your week with swag! 💃
Here’s a quick swing by to share something new and something old ! 
 
❣️New range at @the_bindi_project called TASMAYEE ; after my daughter complained that I didn’t have a variant named after her!❤️

❣️I’m wearing this Kasuti embroidered ilkal silk saree for the 1st time! my Mum in law gave me when I got married 20 years ago! ( so is it old or is it new? 🤔 whichever way you looks at it , I ❤️ it .. ( & I’m going to wear more of it! )

❣️My first crossbody from @pishvi : it’s so sleek and classic , I love it ! It’s my go to & my only all black “bag” I don’t leave home with out my Pishvi 

❣️Nosepins from the Noor Edit . DM for the link🙏🏾

❣️Spot that fab handpainted ring @artsoul_studio
I’ve worn it a lot, maybe I can call it old, coz I need a ”new” one , get it? 😜

❣️At @levitatewithmeghna , I have a thing for jootis. Can never have enough and wears it with everything.
Ooohhh , and did you see the sneak peak at that block print petticoat? I’ve come down to about 3 petticoats I wear with all my sarees! Who else does this? 🤷🏽‍♀️❣️

❣️There’s so much going on in this capture! But then that’s my life and that’s my style! 😂❤️
Let me know what you think?

I have a confession to make!😬
🤷🏽‍♀️What if I told you that I don’t care about Gucci or Gabbana ?
🤷🏽‍♀️ I’m not impressed with that LV Bagvati?
🤷🏽‍♀️ It’s not the shiny high street but the secrets that intrigue me❣️

💕What if I told you that I’m  not chasing international labels, I’m rooting for homegrown heroes! 🙌🏾
 💕Desi brands that bring style, soul, and sustainability to the table get my love all the way 🙌🏾

💕I’m loud , proud  desi at heart who’s vocal for local . I’m sustainable by choice. and I’m obsessed with Indian-made  enterprises that are changing lives and offering serious value  and easy sass! 🙌🏾

💕if you’re seeing this , Go vocal for local! 📢 
Tag your fav Homegrown brand . They could do with a shout out! ❣️

I’m wearing this dress / kurta with hand done Soof embroidery by @rangsutracrafts 

The beaten brass Nosepin in from @chiuclothing @thechiustore , the earrings are from @manasghoraiofficial the Cross body is my faithful @pishvi and the upcycled zero waste glam Bindi is upcycled leather sourced from @pishvi for the G a i a range of @the_bindi_project ❣️
